{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"header","type":"text","text":"## Multi-object UAP observations\n\nThe collection's incidents almost evenly split between ==single-object== and ==multi-object== events. The multi-object events deserve grouped analysis because:\n\n- Loose formations suggest either coordinated platforms or persistent local activity\n- Two-object pairs with one circling the other (D58) are particularly anomalous\n- Multiple events in a short window from a single platform (D65: 3 events) suggest local persistence\n\nThis canvas groups all readable multi-object observations.","x":-1300,"y":-500,"width":700,"height":420,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"single","type":"text","text":"## SINGLE OBJECT (excluded)\n\nNot shown here:\nD4, D6, D7, D8, D38, D44, D50 tearlines, D55, D57, D60, D62 (UAP event), D64 (one of two)\n\nSee individual incident notes.","x":-500,"y":-500,"width":380,"height":260,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"two","type":"text","text":"## TWO-OBJECT pairs","x":-400,"y":-100,"width":250,"height":80,"color":"3"},
